        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Beautiful Perl feature: low-precedence boolean operators 'and', 'or']]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[The elegant usefulness of Perl's low-precedence boolean operators (and, or, not) compared to the more common high-precedence operators (&&, ||, !) is further explored by Laurent. The post shows how the low-precedence boolean operator can be used as a "control flow tool" creating readable, idiomatic code using the example of the classic "do or die" convention.]]></description>
            <pubDate>2026.05.09</pubDate>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://dev.to/damil/beautiful-perl-feature-low-precedence-boolean-operators-and-or-3900</guid>
            <link>https://dev.to/damil/beautiful-perl-feature-low-precedence-boolean-operators-and-or-3900</link>
            
            
            
